remarks.para:
It is highly recommended to call  for returned capture explicitly:

using (var capture = bodyFrame.Capture)
{
    // working with capture
}

But  object automatically tracks all  objects it returned. And will call 
for all of them if client code didn't it.

It is highly recommended to call  for returned image explicitly:

using (var bodyIndexMap = bodyFrame.BodyIndexMap)
{
    // working with body index map
}

But  object automatically tracks all  objects it returned. And will call 
for all of them if client code didn't it.

member.returns:
 if a data block is returned,
or  if the end of the recording is reached.
All other failures will return .

 if a data block is returned,
or  if the start of the recording is reached.
All other failures will return .

remarks.para:
It is highly recommended to call  for returned image explicitly:

using (var colorImage = capture.ColorImage)
{
    if (colorImage != null)
    {
        // working with color image
    }
}

But  object automatically tracks all  objects it returned. And will call 
for all of them if client code didn't it.

It is highly recommended to call  for returned image explicitly:

